sols_latex:
Let

\begin{align*}
v_{AB} = B-A = \begin{bmatrix}1 & 0 & 3 \end{bmatrix} - \begin{bmatrix}0 & 1 & 2 \end{bmatrix} = \begin{bmatrix}1 & -1 & 1 \end{bmatrix}
\end{align*}

and let

\begin{align*}
v_{AC} = C-A = \begin{bmatrix}1 & 1 & 4 \end{bmatrix} - \begin{bmatrix}0 & 1 & 2 \end{bmatrix}  = \begin{bmatrix}1 & 0 & 2 \end{bmatrix}
\end{align*}

Then, the area of a triangle is given by

\begin{align*}
\text{Area} &= 1/2\|v_{AB}\times v_{AC}\|
\end{align*}

Computing the cross product gives

\begin{align*}
v_{AB}\times v_{AC} = \begin{bmatrix} -2 & -1 & 1 \end{bmatrix}
\end{align*}

Taking the norm and dividing by 2 yields

\begin{align*}
\text{Area} &= 1/2\|v_{AB}\times v_{AC}\| = 1/2 \|\begin{bmatrix} -2 & -1 & 1 \end{bmatrix}\| = \frac{\sqrt{(-2)^2 + (-1)^2 + 1^2}}{2} = \frac{\sqrt{6}}{2}
\end{align*}

